  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators are aimed to develop and externally validate a prediction model of clinical&#xD;
      risk factors that quantifies postoperative death after emergency surgery.&#xD;
&#xD;
      The investigators identify all patients treated with emergency surgery, between 2000 and&#xD;
      2020, within the Wuhan Union hospital and all collaborators. The surgical patient cohort will&#xD;
      be matched with the National Death database to determine the patient's postoperative death&#xD;
      data.&#xD;
&#xD;
      60% patients were randomly selected to the development cohort. Logistic regression analysis&#xD;
      for prediction of postoperative death adjusted for different covariates. The model was&#xD;
      externally validated in the remaining 40% patients.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
